 And Then There Was Three ***Meridian Spoilers Inside***

***?MERIDIAN?SPOILERS BELOW***
.
.
.
.
.
.
Well we only 5 ish hours to go till old Doc Jackson is no more....awwwwww! If you want to know about the episode look below.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
?MERIDIAN?
An accident threatens thousands of people on the planet, and Daniel sacrifices himself to save them -- exposing himself to massive radiation. Back in the SGC infirmary, Jackson lays dying. He is saved by Oma Desala, a powerful alien being (and guardian of Shifu, the Harcesis child) who Daniel first met in Season Three's "Maternal Instinct." Oma arrives and helps him ascend beyond his mortal body (a process we've also seen with Shifu in Season Four's "Absolute Power," and Orlin in this year's "Ascension").
.
.
.
***Bigger Spoilers here***
.
.
.
.
.
.
Teal'c is standing in Daniel's office. The lighting is sort of fuzzy and it seems to be a dream sequence of some kind. Daniel is standing by his desk going through some paperwork while Teal'c is standing closeby, nearly in tears.

Teal'c says: "If you are to die, Daniel Jackson, I wish you to know that I believe that the fight against the Goa'uld will have lost one of its greatest warriors."

Daniel pauses for a moment as if he hears Teal'c, but it almost seems as if he can't see that Teal'c is there.
Then there is a flash (dream sequence over), and Teal'c is standing in the infirmary looking down (presumably at Daniel, since there are beeping noises from the medical equipment, even though we don't see him)

Teal'c says: "And I will have lost one of my greatest friends!"
